1
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:52,160
Little Phupha,
come stay with Grandma, okay?

2
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:55,040
Mom.

3
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:58,320
I want to raise Phupha myself.

4
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:03,120
<i>How are the two of you going to raise him?</i>
<i>This isn't easy, you know.</i>

5
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:06,320
I'm wiping you so you'll feel comfortable.

6
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,240
Oon,

7
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:17,720
don't scream.
He hasn't finished peeing yet.

8
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,680
- Fun.
- Hmm?

9
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:31,440
I just dreamt about Nueng.

10
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,520
You dreamt about Nueng?

11
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,120
I dreamt she came to see me.

12
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:44,320
She thanked us and asked us
to take care of Phupha for her.

13
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,640
Nueng must've been
really worried about Phupha.

14
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:02,520
If only she were still alive…

15
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,920
Nueng's at peace now.

16
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,920
Oh, Oon-oon,

17
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,120
what should we do
about the will Nueng left behind?

18
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,800
I, NUBNUNG SIRIPITICHOTE, DECLARE THAT
MY ASSETS SHALL BE DISTRIBUTED AS FOLLOWS:

19
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:34,880
1. CASH DEPOSIT AT MT BANK: 5,580,000 BAHT

20
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,920
2. LAND IN PHETCHABUN: 10 RAI
3. ALL PERSONAL JEWELRY

21
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:44,000
Would you mind

22
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,840
if I kept everything
as Phupha's inheritance?

23
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:51,920
As for all his expenses,
I'll take care of them myself.

24
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,400
Of course. I don't mind at all.

25
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,120
Do whatever you think is right.

26
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:03,240
Then I'll find a lawyer
to handle all of this.

27
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:04,960
Okay.

28
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:10,560
But right now,
shouldn't you go change your shirt first?

29
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:15,680
Good idea.
Please watch the baby for me, okay?

30
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,640
Did he fall asleep already?

31
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,120
My little boy.

32
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,440
Come on.

33
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:59,160
Oon, Oon, you're late.

34
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,520
I'm late? I'm late.

35
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,480
I'm late.

36
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,320
I know you're pretending to sleep.

37
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,880
Come on, get up.

38
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:22,600
Let's go wash your face and brush your
teeth, so we can take Mommy Oon to work.

39
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,160
Okay.

40
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:27,680
Alright. Let's go.

41
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:32,600
Right, left, right, left, right, left.

42
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:37,640
Turn around. Okay.

43
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:44,080
I'm going to look at schools for Phupha.
Any place you want me to check out?

44
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,800
You can decide.

45
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,040
Come here, let me kiss your cheek.

46
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,240
I'm going to work now, okay?

47
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,480
Bye-bye, Mommy Oon.

48
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,800
Bye-bye.

49
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,160
Bye-bye.

50
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:22,160
I'm home.

51
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,760
Phu, I'm back.

52
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:28,280
- Hello, Mommy Oon.
- Hello, sweetheart.

53
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,680
Let me kiss your cheek.

54
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,080
Oon-oon.

55
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:35,200
- Come look at Phupha's school.
- Okay.

56
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:37,120
Today I enrolled him in a school.

57
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,840
It's a bilingual school.

58
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,200
That's great.

59
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:48,760
And look. This is Phupha's uniform.

60
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:53,240
- It's so cool.
- He's gonna look so handsome in this.

61
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,080
School starts next month already.

62
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,360
I'm excited for him.

63
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,760
Then,

64
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:07,680
I'll go put the uniform away first.
Stay with him, okay?

65
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,960
- Sure. Hurry back down.
- Okay.

66
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,480
Wanna race cars with me?

67
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,680
Vroom!

68
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,160
You've grown up
another step already, my baby.

69
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,840
Hello.

70
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

71
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,640
Come on.

72
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:58,920
Wow. My little boy looks
so handsome in this uniform.

73
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Let me see. Alright.

74
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,040
Fun,

75
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:09,600
if we don't let him go now,

76
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,520
he's going to be late for school.

77
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:20,000
Okay. Come on.
Study hard, okay, sweetheart?

78
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,120
Okay.

79
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,920
Be a good boy, okay?

80
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,520
- Okay.
- Bye-bye.

81
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,680
Bye-bye.

82
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:28,880
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

83
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,760
Say hello to the teacher.

84
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,919
- Hello.
- Good morning, Teacher.

85
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:59,480
Oon-oon, our baby
didn't even turn around to look at us.

86
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,960
That's because our son is brave.
He didn't cry at all.

87
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:10,200
You need to stay strong too.

88
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,080
Fun,

89
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,400
should we head back now?
I still have to go to the office.

90
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,880
Come on, come on.

91
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:30,640
Come on, don't be fussy.
Even our son wasn't.

92
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:02,280
MORNING 06:00 A.M. - 08:50 A.M.
EVENING 03:00 P.M. - 06:00 P.M.

93
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:53,080
SEARCH LOCATION

94
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,720
You've never really been
away from him, have you?

95
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,720
PAFUN'S LOCATION

96
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,320
PAFUN

97
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,440
<i>Yes, Oon?</i>

98
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:06,880
So, how's our son doing?

99
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:11,000
Do you want me to enroll you there too?

100
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:13,720
Oon-oon…

101
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:18,120
So what time are you heading home?

102
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,480
School will be over in a few hours.

103
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,160
I think I'll just wait and pick him up.

104
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,760
Okay.

105
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,640
- <i>Bye-bye.</i>
- Bye.

106
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:51,040
Here, fried chicken.

107
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,120
I want your fried chicken.

108
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,360
This is the same.

109
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,840
I don't think it is.

110
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:21,640
Yours is darker. This one's lighter.

111
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,480
Is this one not good?

112
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,280
Yours tastes better.

113
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:34,520
Then I'll make it
for you another day, okay?

114
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,840
Okay.

115
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:40,040
But for today, eat this one first, okay?

116
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,400
I'm home.

117
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:59,960
- Mommy Oon.
- Yes?

118
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,600
So how was school today? Was it fun?

119
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,040
It was fun. There were lots of toys.

120
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:09,560
You must've been so happy.
Play hard, but study hard too, okay?

121
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,560
Okay.

122
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:16,440
Alright. Up you go.

123
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,400
Go.

124
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,000
Study hard, my baby.

125
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:42,240
Mommy, you can go home now.
You don't have to stay and watch me.

126
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:44,560
Oh? You don't want me to stay?

127
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:48,240
No. You should go home.

128
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:51,840
I want fried pork. Can you make it for me?

129
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:55,200
Fried pork? Of course, sweetheart.

130
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,040
- Thank you.
- Alright.

131
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,160
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

132
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:12,040
- Hello.
- Hello.

133
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:43,640
- Mommy Fun.
- My boy.

134
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:46,360
- Hello.
- Hello.

135
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:47,880
Let's go home.

136
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,880
Yes.

137
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:53,920
I'm home.

138
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,440
He's asleep.

139
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:16,720
Phupha, sweetheart, wake up and eat.

140
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,200
Phu.

141
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:24,560
Should we let him sleep a little longer?
He can eat after he wakes up.

142
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:28,440
No. He needs to eat on time,
or he'll get gastritis.

143
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:34,000
Phupha, come on.

144
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,560
Let's eat.

145
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,880
Where's my fried pork?

146
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:51,560
Here it is. Fried pork.

147
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,840
Why doesn't it look the same?

148
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,280
I bought this one today.

149
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:06,800
It's crispy on the outside too.
It's yummy.

150
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:11,240
No. I said I wanted you to make it.

151
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:14,040
Why didn't you make it?

152
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:28,480
Phupha, don't fuss, okay?
Can you eat this one first today?

153
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,560
It's not the same.

154
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:35,240
I want the fried pork without crispy bits.

155
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:45,400
Phu, do you love Mommy Fun?

156
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,640
Yes.

157
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:51,920
Today, she went out and specially bought
this fried pork with crispy bits for you.

158
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:56,520
But if you don't eat it,
Mommy Fun will be sad.

159
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:59,280
Look, she is about to cry.

160
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,800
See?

161
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:11,599
I'm sorry, Mommy Fun. I'll eat it.

162
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,319
I'm sorry too, Phu.

163
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:24,640
Tomorrow, I'll make both fried pork
and fried chicken for you. How about that?

164
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:31,000
No. I want fried pork tomorrow.
Fried chicken can be another day.

165
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,760
Okay.

166
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:36,600
Then shall we eat now?

167
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,920
Okay.

168
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:39,920
Come on.

169
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,600
Try the fried pork first, okay?

170
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,880
Open your mouth.

171
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,560
Not sleepy yet?

172
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,880
I've been thinking about Phupha.

173
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:29,160
I feel really bad
for hurting his feelings.

174
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,600
I forgot that when I was little,

175
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:35,200
whenever my parents promised me
something and didn't do it,

176
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,920
I felt terrible every single time.

177
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:42,320
But today, I didn't think about how he
would feel and did the exact same thing,

178
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,360
even though I've been through it myself.

179
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,360
Fun,

180
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,480
I understand.

181
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:01,760
Don't blame yourself.

182
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:09,480
We'll start over tomorrow.

183
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:13,680
I don't even know where to start.

184
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,920
Normally,

185
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,720
in the evenings,
you make food that Phupha likes.

186
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:24,160
But because you spent all your time
waiting for him at school,

187
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,920
you missed doing those little things

188
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:30,200
- Aioon.
- Easy now.

189
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:32,360
Don't get upset yet.

190
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:40,280
Hear me out first, then think

191
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:44,080
about whether what I'm saying makes sense.

192
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,160
If you don't know where to start,

193
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:58,160
then start with the normal things
that were already good

194
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,840
and make them even better.

195
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:01,640
Normal things?

196
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:04,000
I mean the normal things

197
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:07,120
before Phupha started school.

198
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,200
Thank you. Let's go to sleep.

199
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,840
- Good night.
- Oh, Fun?

200
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,520
That's it?

201
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,840
Sleep. Tomorrow, I have
to take our son to school early.

202
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:35,960
But… but I did a good deed.

203
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,800
Aioon. Sleep now.

204
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,160
Good night.

205
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:04,080
Good night.

206
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:17,800
Oon-oon.

207
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:23,840
- Hello, Oon.
- Hello.

208
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,960
Hello, Aunt Pa.

209
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,400
Hello, Phupha.

210
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,360
Hello.

211
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:32,160
- Aunt Wi asked me to bring snacks over.
- Thank you.

212
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,160
How have you been, Pa?

213
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:38,960
I've been well. Aunt Wi sends her regards
to both of you

214
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,400
and Phupha too.

215
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,680
Thank you.

216
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,400
So how's Aunt Wi's relative doing?

217
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,560
Still about the same,
sometimes better, sometimes worse.

218
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,800
Aunt Wi has to stay there
and take care of her.

219
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,000
- Mommy.
- Yes?

220
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:58,640
A cat.

221
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,440
A cat?

222
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:05,760
Whose cat is this? Why is it here?

223
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,600
Oh, Mr. Jorn.

224
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:10,760
So besides going to my house,
you come to this house too?

225
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,680
Is this your cat, Pa?

226
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:18,120
The security guard said it belonged to
someone in the neighborhood behind ours.

227
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:21,040
They moved away but left the cat behind.

228
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:24,400
Oh, no.

229
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:32,000
Mommy Oon, can Mr. Jorn stay at our house?

230
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:41,200
Phu, what if the owner comes back

231
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:44,880
and can't find Mr. Jorn?
They'll be sad, you know.

232
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:48,000
Aunt Pa said they abandoned him.

233
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,840
He can sleep in my room.

234
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:03,400
I'll even share half my food with him.

235
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:23,080
Okay, sweetheart. Don't cry.
You can keep him.

236
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,280
But there's one condition.

237
00:23:28,360 --> 00:23:32,440
You have to take care of Mr. Jorn
and be responsible for him.

238
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:37,600
And after you finish playing,
you have to put your toys away.

239
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:40,840
- Okay?
- Yes, I can do it.

240
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,960
Thank you. Thank you.

241
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:46,000
- Alright.
- Okay.

242
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:48,920
Mr. Jorn, come live with us now.

243
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:51,440
Congratulations.

244
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:54,440
Now you're not
Mr. Jorn the stray cat anymore.

245
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,360
Fruit for you.

246
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,600
Thank you.

247
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,120
Mommies,

248
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,960
Mr. Jorn won't eat.

249
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:21,200
He didn't eat yesterday, and he didn't
eat today either. He sleeps all the time.

250
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:26,760
I think we should take Mr. Jorn
to the vet. He can get his vaccines too.

251
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,280
Okay.

252
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:40,120
Oh, Mr. Jorn.

253
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:42,440
- You know him?
- Yes.

254
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,160
We already have his records here.

255
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:50,360
But back then, his owner…

256
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:54,840
They moved away.
We're taking care of him now.

257
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,040
Okay.

258
00:24:56,120 --> 00:25:01,280
Then I'll update the records
to show that you're Mr. Jorn's owners.

259
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:02,480
Okay.

260
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,840
So what brings Mr. Jorn in today?

261
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,920
Mr. Jorn hasn't eaten for two days.

262
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:11,800
He didn't eat yesterday, and he didn't
eat today either. He just keeps sleeping.

263
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:14,400
Alright, let me take a look.

264
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:17,960
Alright.

265
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,560
Let me check.

266
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:32,400
Could I ask something too?

267
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:34,720
When does he need his next vaccines

268
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:37,240
and flea treatment?

269
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,160
Just a moment. Let me check.

270
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:45,720
Well, the vaccines
are due near the end of the year.

271
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,240
As for the flea treatment,
he can get that today.

272
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:49,680
Then please do that.

273
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:50,720
Of course.

274
00:25:51,920 --> 00:25:56,360
I'd like to run a blood test. According
to his records, he has a blood disorder

275
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:59,200
and needs medication
to increase his platelet count.

276
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,960
But for today,
I'll give him vitamins first

277
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:05,680
and apply the flea treatment.
Please wait outside first.

278
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,000
- Okay.
- Alright.

279
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:09,880
Come on, baby.

280
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:11,800
Wait a moment.

281
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,920
PAFUN

282
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,040
Yes?

283
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,120
<i>Oon-oon, can you talk right now?</i>

284
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,760
Yes.

285
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:44,720
I prepared dinner. It's in the cabinet.
Make sure Phupha eats on time.

286
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:48,320
I also cut some fruit. It's on the second
shelf from the bottom in the fridge.

287
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:49,840
Okay.

288
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:52,680
You don't have to fold the clothes
in the dryer. I'll do it when I get back.

289
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:53,800
Just focus on taking care of our son.

290
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:56,560
<i>And Mr. Jorn's wet food,</i>
<i>I already put it in the cabinet.</i>

291
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:58,400
<i>I already cleaned the cat litter too.</i>

292
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:00,520
- <i>And also--</i>
- Fun.

293
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:03,680
I can take care of our son. Don't worry.

294
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:06,320
<i>You can go to work.</i>

295
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,400
Are you sure?

296
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,400
Very sure.

297
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:19,040
Mommy Fun's back!

298
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:26,200
What happened to your face?
And what are you all playing?

299
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:27,880
- Where's Mommy Oon?
- Inside.

300
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:30,080
Aioon! Aioon!

301
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,920
Yes?

302
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:38,600
What are you all doing? And Mr. Jorn too?

303
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:41,520
Oon.

304
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:43,920
What is this?

305
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:49,240
Well, Phupha wanted to play doctor,
so Jorn and I became the patients.

306
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:57,880
Go take a shower right now. All of you.

307
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:59,360
Take Mr. Jorn with you too, Oon.

308
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,600
- Phu, wait.
- Take him with you.

309
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:03,600
- Aioon.
- I'm going.

310
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:09,440
What is this?

311
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,960
Aioon!

312
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:29,040
Aioon. What exactly happened here?

313
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:31,960
We were just playing.

314
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:38,200
Just playing?

315
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,280
The house is a mess. Everyone's filthy.

316
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:43,160
What was all that?

317
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:47,600
Mommy Fun, don't scold Mommy Oon.

318
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:51,760
I wanted to be a doctor,
so Mommy Oon played with me.

319
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,120
I was just playing with him.

320
00:28:56,600 --> 00:29:00,200
We got a little too carried away.

321
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:05,360
But I was doing it all
for his development.

322
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:12,120
Mommy Fun, don't scold Mommy Oon.

323
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:15,160
When I grow up, I'm going to be a doctor.

324
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:23,360
You want to be a doctor? Really?

325
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:27,120
I'm going to be a doctor
who treats Mr. Jorn.

326
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:30,680
When Mr. Jorn gets sick,
I'll be able to treat him myself.

327
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,040
Can I do that?

328
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:39,160
Of course you can.
I'll help guide you there.

329
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,320
Okay.

330
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:56,280
PREPARING YOUR CHILD TO BE A DOCTOR

331
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,680
A GUIDE FOR PARENTS

332
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:13,320
Phupha, hurry and eat, sweetheart.

333
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:16,600
After this, we'll continue
on the path to becoming a doctor.

334
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:21,240
Again? It's been days already.
When will we get there?

335
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:26,320
We'll get there eventually.
We'll take it step by step, okay?

336
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:28,760
It's taking forever.

337
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,720
Hurry and eat, sweetheart.

338
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,480
Okay, let's try adding numbers.

339
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,840
- What number is this?
- Two.

340
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,840
- And what symbol is this?
- Plus.

341
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,040
- And what number is this?
- Three.

342
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:52,240
Good. Now try adding them together.
What do you get?

343
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:55,520
- One, two, three, four, five.
- Five.

344
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:59,640
Next one. What number is this?

345
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:06,560
Now how about this one? Can you do it?

346
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,840
Sit down. I will teach you.

347
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:24,280
Okay, if it goes over ten,
you have to keep six in your head first.

348
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,360
How do I keep it in my head?

349
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:31,840
Keep six in your mind first.
Then hold up seven fingers.

350
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,320
Six, then what comes next?

351
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:38,360
Seven, eight, nine, ten,
eleven, twelve, thirteen.

352
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,840
Very good.

353
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:43,280
Now do the next question first, okay?
I'll be right back.

354
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:57,160
Phupha, I'm home.

355
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:02,440
- Hello, Mommy Oon.
- Hello.

356
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:09,920
Fourteen, fifteen, sixteen,
seventeen, eighteen, nineteen, twenty,

357
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,360
twenty-one, twenty-two…

358
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,560
Eighteen, nineteen…

359
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:40,760
Phu? Phu, what's wrong?

360
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:45,440
It hurts here, and here, and here.

361
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:48,520
That's called a headache.
You have a headache, right?

362
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:53,560
Okay, it's alright.
I'll get some medicine. Wait a second.

363
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:00,560
Oon?

364
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:03,520
He has a headache.

365
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:07,040
How did he suddenly get a headache?
He was fine.

366
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:09,840
You stay with him first.
I'll go get some medicine.

367
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,600
Phupha.

368
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:20,800
What's wrong, sweetheart?

369
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,520
My head hurts here.

370
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:23,800
Come here.

371
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,640
Come here, sweetheart.

372
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:31,280
It's okay.

373
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:39,560
Take your medicine first.
Then you'll feel better.

374
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:44,200
No need to feed me. I can do it myself.

375
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:52,760
Here's some water.

376
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:02,640
- Good boy.
- Very good. Very good.

377
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:52,480
Fun, is Phupha asleep already?

378
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,440
Yes.

379
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:02,680
We need to talk.

380
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:04,960
Come here.

381
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:24,960
I agree with supporting our son's dreams.

382
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,400
But…

383
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:35,480
I think some things
are just too much for a child his age.

384
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:44,240
I know now. The reason he got a headache

385
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:48,440
was because I pushed him too hard.

386
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:56,280
I'm a terrible mother, aren't I?

387
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,960
Not at all.

388
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:03,160
You're a good mother.

389
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:10,000
You were just rushing things too much.

390
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,560
I'm scared…

391
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,240
Scared?

392
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:18,880
I'm scared
I won't raise Phupha well enough.

393
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:20,760
I'm scared he won't grow up
to be successful.

394
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:23,760
I want him to have a good future.

395
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:26,800
That's why I keep trying to support him.

396
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:29,080
Fun.

397
00:36:30,560 --> 00:36:34,440
I think it's too early.

398
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:37,280
He's only in kindergarten.

399
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:40,960
But our family is a family
with two moms, Oon.

400
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:46,320
I don't want anyone looking down on him,
don't want him to feel inferior to anyone.

401
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:52,160
Don't you think you're overthinking this?

402
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:57,200
I'm not overthinking it, Oon.
Do you remember

403
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:59,680
everything the two of us
had to go through?

404
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:01,720
To be here today,

405
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:05,880
to finally make
the people around us accept us,

406
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,320
what did we have to go through?

407
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:11,040
And now,

408
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:14,280
we have to raise our son

409
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:18,840
on our own.

410
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:24,960
I don't know what kind of questions
Phupha will face growing up.

411
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,120
That's true.

412
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:40,040
But now I understand.
I'll take it slow from now on.

413
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,640
We'll fix things one step at a time.

414
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,800
I agree.

415
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:54,440
We should support him
at the stage he's ready for.

416
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:59,760
Before this, he wanted to be an engineer.

417
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:02,160
Now he wants to be a doctor.

418
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:06,040
In the future,
maybe he'll want to be a teacher,

419
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:09,840
or a businessman or an influencer.

420
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:13,600
But no matter what he becomes,

421
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:19,360
I think it's enough if he grows up
to be a good person

422
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:23,000
and has a career that can support him

423
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:25,880
after the two of us are gone.

424
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:36,080
But right now,

425
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:41,480
I think there's something more worrying.

426
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:45,640
What is it?

427
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:50,520
Phupha's birthday is coming up soon.

428
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:56,080
As he grows older

429
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:01,960
and finds out that his birthday

430
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,560
is also the day his mother died…

431
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:10,360
how are we going to explain that to him?

432
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,960
I think when the time comes,

433
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:26,280
we'll find a way.

434
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:30,960
Once Phupha is old enough to understand,

435
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:33,840
I'll give him Nueng's letter to read.

436
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:38,560
Then he'll know
just how much his mother loved him.

437
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:43,240
And if anything else happens after that,

438
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:45,880
we'll deal with it one step at a time.

439
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:49,240
Like we always have.

440
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,040
Hello.

441
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:14,680
- Hello, sweetheart.
- Hello.

442
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:16,320
Let's go home. Did you have fun?

443
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,880
Yes.

444
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,560
Mommy Fun,

445
00:40:26,640 --> 00:40:30,080
after dinner,
do I have to go sit at that table again?

446
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,920
No more, sweetheart.

447
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:37,320
We're not continuing
the doctor journey anymore?

448
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,240
We're taking a break
from the journey for now.

449
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:48,160
When you get older,
we'll continue the journey, okay?

450
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,040
Yay!

451
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:52,280
- Mommy Oon?
- Yes?

452
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:55,320
What are we gonna do after dinner?

453
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:58,840
How about we go play with Mr. Jorn?

454
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,000
Good.

455
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:09,080
We won't make a mess like that day.

456
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:11,640
Right?

457
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:16,000
Come on. Finish your food first.

458
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:14,880
Mommy Fun, today's my birthday.

459
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,320
Mommy Fun.

460
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:25,000
Mommy Oon, it's my birthday today.

461
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:31,720
Happy birthday!

462
00:44:39,560 --> 00:44:42,320
Fun, it's almost time to give alms.

463
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:43,240
Let's go make merit.

464
00:44:43,320 --> 00:44:45,080
I already prepared everything.

465
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:47,680
- Let's go offer food to the monks.
- Yes.

466
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:49,800
Go change clothes.

467
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:53,720
Birthday. Birthday.

468
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:57,160
Let's go.

469
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:07,400
No strength in your hands today?

470
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:13,600
Get well soon.

471
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:18,080
Fun.

472
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:28,640
Please receive this blessing.

473
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:31,560
For those who always respect
and honor their elders,

474
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:34,800
four blessings shall flourish.

475
00:45:34,880 --> 00:45:37,440
Long life, beauty, happiness,

476
00:45:37,520 --> 00:45:40,400
and strength. May you be blessed.

477
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:43,280
Sathu. Okay.

478
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:47,440
Mother, I'm five years old now.

479
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:50,280
I'll be a good boy and study hard.

480
00:45:50,360 --> 00:45:52,600
I made merit for you today, Mother.

481
00:46:39,040 --> 00:46:42,280
- Alright.
- Let's blow out the candles together.

482
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:45,840
Does it look yummy?

483
00:47:09,240 --> 00:47:11,240
Yeah!

484
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:18,120
Happy birthday, sweetheart.

485
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:21,960
I hope you grow up to be a good boy,

486
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:25,720
healthy in both body and heart.

487
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:26,680
Thank you.

488
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:32,800
I hope you'll always be surrounded
by people who love you like this.

489
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:33,760
Thank you.

490
00:47:36,120 --> 00:47:37,760
Let's take a photo.

491
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:43,200
- Let's take a photo.
- Okay. Come on.

492
00:47:43,280 --> 00:47:44,280
Come on.

493
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:56,280
Phu, smile.

494
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:57,960
Take it.

495
00:48:21,120 --> 00:48:24,600
<i>From now on, no matter what happens,</i>

496
00:48:24,680 --> 00:48:26,640
<i>we'll hold hands</i>

497
00:48:26,720 --> 00:48:28,680
<i>and get through it together.</i>

498
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:41,040
THE END

499
00:49:41,480 --> 00:49:44,280
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
